article.description: Katie McWilliams scored 29 points and Sydney Wiese added 17 as No. 25 Oregon State rolled to an 88-56 victory over Lamar on Friday.
article.headline: No. 25 Oregon St. women stretch home-win streak, beat Lamar
article.linkText: No. 25 Oregon St. women stretch home-win streak, beat Lamar
article.story:
CORVALIS, Ore. --  Katie McWilliams scored 29 points and Sydney Wiese added 17 as No. 25 Oregon State rolled to an 88-56 victory over Lamar on Friday.

The Beavers, coming off their first NCAA Final Four appearance, have won 13 straight home games.

McWilliams was 11 of 14 from the field and 7 of 7 from 3-point range. Wiese made 6 of 7 field-goal attempts, including five 3-pointers. Marie Gulich added 12 points and Gabriella Hanson had seven assists, three steals and chipped in four points for Oregon State.

Wiese made a 3-pointer with about a minute left in the first quarter to give the Beavers a double-digit lead.  Oregon State used an 11-1 run to stretch its lead 30-16 midway through the second quarter.

Moe Kinard scored 12 points and Kiandra Bowers had nine points, 10 rebounds, and five steals to lead Lamar.

It was the first meeting between the schools.
